    "body": "### Problem\n\nI encountered an assertion failure while using Neovim. The editor crashed abruptly with an assertion failure. This happens during normal usage.\n\nnvim: /var/tmp/portage/app-editors/neovim-0.12.2/work/neovim-0.12.2/src/nvim/decoration.c:1078: buf_signcols_count_range: Assertion `buf->b_signcols.count[prevwidth - 1] >= 0' failed\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nI don't have a specific reproducible example. I was doing regular text editing when Neovim suddenly crashed with this assertion failure.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nNot to crash.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.2 Build type: Release LuaJIT 2.1.1780076327\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nI don't know\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nGentoo linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nEmerge",
